&#8232;This course covers the archaeology of the complex societies of the Old and New Worlds from the end of the paleolithic up to and including the earliest civilizations.&#8232;

&#8232;Students agreed that this course was “straightforward,” saying that the topics were “interesting,” but the lectures themselves did not always “stimulate interest.” Students say that the class could benefit from occasional quizzes so that they can get an idea of their grades before the big exams.&#8232;
&#8232;Students felt Professor Zettler was a “great person and interesting teacher.”&#8232;&#8232;

Students agreed that the work was “easy” and the workload reasonable. Some felt that the work was repetitive at times and that “some of the required readings should be shortened.” This course fulfills the History and Tradition sector requirement.
